  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature. The properties of this item are affixed to a piece of armor.)</em></p><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>What appears to be a little more than an ordinary flak jacket carries special impact insulation that upon activation allows him to survive many otherwise deadly blows to his chest cavity such as projectiles, explosions, and blunt trauma.</p><p>While attuned, the combat jack magically merges with an <strong>armor</strong> of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, and requires 10 minutes to complete.</p><p><strong>Effect</strong>: Any time a creatures expends a charge or dice as part of a feature, they gain temporary hit points equal to the die roll. This is considered one source of temporary hit points, so the amount can increase if there are temporary hit points already remaining.</p>",
